Step 2: Big Picture


"I use the Sliding Window approach. I expand the window until it contains all three characters. 
Once it becomes valid, I count all valid substrings starting from the current left pointer."
I use a frequency array to store how many a, b, and c are inside the current window."
"When all three frequencies are greater than zero, it means my current window contains a, b, and c, so it is valid."
"I move the right pointer and add the current character to the window."
